<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-02-15T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-02-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/12395: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-15T20:00:00-05:00">February 15, 1938—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>142. Your 239, February 11, noon. No further action would appear to be
                            called for except to suggest to American claimants the preparation of
                            claims covering any property losses sustained as a result of acts of
                            Japanese forces at Wuhu.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>